# Bilingual Convention

All written content in this repository must follow a strict bilingual (EN/RU) convention.

## Code Comments

**All inline and doc comments in Go source files must be in English.**

```go
// ✅ GOOD
// User is the central domain entity.
// GORM tags are a pragmatic compromise to support AutoMigrate.
type User struct { ... }

// ❌ BAD
// User — центральная доменная сущность.
type User struct { ... }
```

## Example Packages

The `examples/` directory always contains two parallel versions:

- `examples/clean_package_example_en/` — full example with **English** comments
- `examples/clean_package_example_ru/` — same code with **Russian** comments

When adding a new example package, always create both `_en` and `_ru` variants.

## Documentation Files

Docs are split into two locale folders:

```
docs/
├── en/   ← primary, English
└── ru/   ← Russian translation, kept in sync with en/
```

When updating `docs/en/*.md`, also update the matching file in `docs/ru/`.

## README

- `README.md` — English (canonical)
- `README.ru.md` — Russian translation

When updating `README.md`, reflect the changes in `README.ru.md`.

## Obsidian Notes

Obsidian notes in the vault are written in **Russian** (they are internal
development logs, not public documentation).
